        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 2:52PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 251 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Idabel, or 23 miles west of Horatio, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Eagletown, Broken Bow, Idabel, Cerrogordo, De Queen, Hochatown,
Harris, Goodwater, Shinewell, Haworth, Holly Creek, Gillham, West
Line, Oak Hill, and West Otis.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for southwestern
Arkansas.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
southwestern Arkansas...southeastern Oklahoma...and northeastern
Texas.</instruction>
